revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tpMldSnoopingEnable.name: tpMldSnoopingEnable
tpMldSnoopingEnable.description: Select Enable/Disable MLD Snooping function globally on the Switch. 0. disable 1. enable

tpMldUnknownMulticastPacket.name: tpMldUnknownMulticastPacket
tpMldUnknownMulticastPacket.description: Select the operation for the switch to process unknown multicast. 0. forward 1. discard

tpMldUnknownReportSuppression.name: tpMldUnknownReportSuppression
tpMldUnknownReportSuppression.description: Select Enable/Disable MLD Snooping report suppression function globally on the Switch. 0. disable 1. enable

tpMldGlobalRouterTime.name: tpMldGlobalRouterTime
tpMldGlobalRouterTime.description: Specify the aging time of the router port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive MLD query message from the router port, it will consider this port is not a router port any more,60-600 second.

tpMldGlobalMemberTime.name: tpMldGlobalMemberTime
tpMldGlobalMemberTime.description: Specify the aging time of the member port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive MLD report message from the member port, it will consider this port is not a member port any more,60-600 second.

tpMldlastListenerQueryInterval.name: tpMldlastListenerQueryInterval
tpMldlastListenerQueryInterval.description: Enter the Last Listener Query interval time. When the multicast group has no more member ports, it will send the Specific Query Message with this interval time to check whether there is another member. The interval is ranging from 1 to 5 seconds.

tpMldlastListenerQueryCount.name: tpMldlastListenerQueryCount
tpMldlastListenerQueryCount.description: Enter the Last Listener Query numbers. When the multicast group has no more member ports, it will send this numbers of Specific Query Message to check whether there is another member. It is ranging from 1 to 5.

tpMldPortTable.name: tpMldPortTable
tpMldPortTable.description: MLD Snooping (Internet Group Management Protocol Snooping) is a multicast control mechanism running on Layer 2 switch. It can effectively prevent multicast groups being broadcasted in the network.

tpMldPortEntry.name: tpMldPortEntry
tpMldPortEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of port configure.

tpMldSnoopingPortEnable.name: tpMldSnoopingPortEnable
tpMldSnoopingPortEnable.description: Select Enable/Disable MLD Snooping for the desired port. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpMldFastLeavePortEnable.name: tpMldFastLeavePortEnable
tpMldFastLeavePortEnable.description: Select Enable/Disable Fast Leave feature for the desired port. If Fast Leave is enabled for a port, the Switch will immediately remove this port from the multicast group upon receiving MLD leave messages. 0. Disable 1. Enable

tpMldPortLag.name: tpMldPortLag
tpMldPortLag.description: Displays the LAG number which the port belongs to.

tpMldVlanTable.name: tpMldVlanTable
tpMldVlanTable.description: Multicast groups established by MLD Snooping are based on VLANs. You can configure different MLD parameters for different VLANs.

tpMldVlanEntry.name: tpMldVlanEntry
tpMldVlanEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of mldsnooping.

tpMldVlanId.name: tpMldVlanId
tpMldVlanId.description: Enter the VLAN ID to enable MLD Snooping for the desired VLAN,1-4094.

tpMldRouterTime.name: tpMldRouterTime
tpMldRouterTime.description: Specify the aging time of the router port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive MLD query message from the router port, it will consider this port is not a router port any more,0,60-600 second.

tpMldMemberTime.name: tpMldMemberTime
tpMldMemberTime.description: Specify the aging time of the member port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive MLD report message from the member port, it will consider this port is not a member port any more,0,60-600 second.

tpMldRouterPort.name: tpMldRouterPort
tpMldRouterPort.description: Config the static router ports which are mainly used in the network with stable topology.

tpMldForbiddenRouterPort.name: tpMldForbiddenRouterPort
tpMldForbiddenRouterPort.description: Config the forbidden router ports which are mainly used to forbidden specified ports to become router ports.

tpMldVlanStatus.name: tpMldVlanStatus
tpMldVlanStatus.description: the following two values are states: these values may be read or written active(1), notInService(2), the following value is a state: this value may be read, but not written notReady(3), the following three values are actions: these values may be written, but are never read createAndGo(4), createAndWait(5), destroy(6)

tpMldMultiVlanId.name: tpMldMultiVlanId
tpMldMultiVlanId.description: Enter the VLAN ID of the multicast VLAN,2-4094.If enter 0, multicast VLAN is disabled.

tpMldMultitRouterTime.name: tpMldMultitRouterTime
tpMldMultitRouterTime.description: Specify the aging time of the router port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive MLD query message from the router port, it will consider this port is not a router port any more,0,60-600 second.

tpMldMultiMemberTime.name: tpMldMultiMemberTime
tpMldMultiMemberTime.description: Specify the aging time of the member port. Within this time, if the switch don't receive MLD report message from the member port, it will consider this port is not a member port any more,0,60-600 second.

tpMldMultiRouterPort.name: tpMldMultiRouterPort
tpMldMultiRouterPort.description: Config the static router ports which are mainly used in the network with stable topology.

tpMldMultiForbiddenRouterPort.name: tpMldMultiForbiddenRouterPort
tpMldMultiForbiddenRouterPort.description: Config the forbidden router ports which are mainly used to forbidden specified ports to become router ports.

tpMldMultiReplaceSrcIp.name: tpMldMultiReplaceSrcIp
tpMldMultiReplaceSrcIp.description: config the source ip which will replace the source ip of MLD report in multicast vlan.

mldQuerierTable.name: mldQuerierTable
mldQuerierTable.description: MLD Snooping Querier is based on VLAN. You can configure different MLD Snooping Querier parameters for different VLANs.

mldQuerierEntry.name: mldQuerierEntry
mldQuerierEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of MLD Snooping Querier.

mldQuerierVlanId.name: mldQuerierVlanId
mldQuerierVlanId.description: Enter the VLAN ID to enable MLD Snooping Querier for the desired VLAN, ranging from 1 to 4094.

mldQueryInterval.name: mldQueryInterval
mldQueryInterval.description: Enter the Query message interval time. The Querier will send General Query Message with this interval. The interval is ranging from 10 to 300 seconds.

mldMaxResponseTime.name: mldMaxResponseTime
mldMaxResponseTime.description: Enter the value of Maximum Response Time field of the Query message. The host is expected to response to an MLD general query within this time. The time is ranging from 1 to 25 seconds.

mldGeneralQuerySrcIp.name: mldGeneralQuerySrcIp
mldGeneralQuerySrcIp.description: Enter the General Query Message source IP address.

mldQuerierStatus.name: mldQuerierStatus
mldQuerierStatus.description: The following values are states: these values may be used as follow: active(1),if the entry is being used. createAndGo(4),not being used. destroy(6),destory the entry.

tpMldFilterPortTable.name: tpMldFilterPortTable
tpMldFilterPortTable.description: When the switch receives MLD report message, it examines the multicast filtering IP ID configured on the access port to determine if the port can join the multicast group. If the multicast IP is not filtered, the switch will add the port to the forward port list of the multicast group. Otherwise, the switch will drop the MLD report message. In that way, you can control the multicast groups that users can access.

tpMldFilterPortEntry.name: tpMldFilterPortEntry
tpMldFilterPortEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of a port param.

tpMldFilterMaxGroup.name: tpMldFilterMaxGroup
tpMldFilterMaxGroup.description: Specify the maximum number of multicast groups to prevent some ports taking up too much bandwidth.

tpMldFilterMaxGroupAction.name: tpMldFilterMaxGroupAction
tpMldFilterMaxGroupAction.description: The policy should be taken when the number of multicast group a port has joined reach the maximum. 0.Drop: drop the successive report packet, and this port can not join any other multicast group. 1.Replace: when the port joins another new multicast group,it will quit the existing multicast group randomly.

tpMldFilterBindAddrId.name: tpMldFilterBindAddrId
tpMldFilterBindAddrId.description: Enter the profile ID the port will be bound to. Only one profile can be bound to each port.

tpMldFilterPortLag.name: tpMldFilterPortLag
tpMldFilterPortLag.description: Displays the LAG number which the port belongs to.

tpMldPktStatTable.name: tpMldPktStatTable
tpMldPktStatTable.description: A list of multicast statistic Table.

tpMldPktStatEntry.name: tpMldPktStatEntry
tpMldPktStatEntry.description: An entry contains of multicast packet statistics over each port.

tpMldQueryPktStat.name: tpMldQueryPktStat
tpMldQueryPktStat.description: Displays the number of query packets the port received.

tpMldReportV1PktStat.name: tpMldReportV1PktStat
tpMldReportV1PktStat.description: Displays the number of MLDv1 report packets the port received.

tpMldReportV2PktStat.name: tpMldReportV2PktStat
tpMldReportV2PktStat.description: Displays the number of MLDv2 report packets the port received.

tpMldDonePktStat.name: tpMldDonePktStat
tpMldDonePktStat.description: Displays the number of done packets the port received.

tpMldErrorPktStat.name: tpMldErrorPktStat
tpMldErrorPktStat.description: Displays the number of error packets the port received.

tpMldMulticastGroupTable.name: tpMldMulticastGroupTable
tpMldMulticastGroupTable.description: A list of multicast groups Table.

tpMldMulticastGroupEntry.name: tpMldMulticastGroupEntry
tpMldMulticastGroupEntry.description: An entry contains of multicast packet statistics over each port.

tpMldForwardPorts.name: tpMldForwardPorts
tpMldForwardPorts.description: Displays the forward ports of multicast group.

tpMldGrouptype.name: tpMldGrouptype
tpMldGrouptype.description: Displays the type of multicast group.

tpMldMulticastStaticGroupTable.name: tpMldMulticastStaticGroupTable
tpMldMulticastStaticGroupTable.description: A list of multicast groups Table.

tpMldMulticastStaticGroupEntry.name: tpMldMulticastStaticGroupEntry
tpMldMulticastStaticGroupEntry.description: An entry contains of multicast packet statistics over each port.

tpMldStaticForwardPorts.name: tpMldStaticForwardPorts
tpMldStaticForwardPorts.description: The forward ports of multicast group.

tpMldStaticGroupStatus.name: tpMldStaticGroupStatus
tpMldStaticGroupStatus.description: The following values are states: these values may be used as follow: active(1),if the entry is being used. notInService(2),destory the entry. notReady(3),destory the entry. createAndGo(4),not being used createAndWait(5),creat a new entry destroy(6),destory the entry.
